snippet.textDisplay: Already 1 minute in, talking about how apartments go really fast, and I had an actual lol. I've lived in NYC for over a year now and am in my second apartment. If the apartment is good, it goes fast, if it is bad, it stays on the market for a long time. My first apartment had been listed for a few weeks, long enough that I was able to schedule a showing TWO WEEKS in advance before my move. I came to realize it was a shitty apartment (got robbed, ceiling constantly leaking/breaking, mice, roaches) and I moved out immediately when my lease was up. I saw the apartment I am currently in get listed, contacted the broker, set up a showing for the next day, and submitted my application and deposit within 30 minutes in a grocery store down the street I came to while exploring the neighborhood.
